Interface MessageBuf<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the messages that are hold by this MessageBuf

    • Method Detail

      • unfoldAndAdd

        boolean unfoldAndAdd(Object o)
        Unfold the specified object if necessary, and then add the unfolded objects (or the specified object if unfonding was not necessary) to this buffer. If the specified object is an object array (Object[]), this method adds the elements of the array to this buffer until null is encountered. If the specified object is null, nothing is added to this buffer. Otherwise, the specified object is added to this buffer as-is.
        Returns:
        true if one or more messages were added to this buffer. false otherwise.
